🔍 Part 1 — How SAML Debugging Actually Works

When debugging SAML, you must inspect:

SAML Request (AuthnRequest)

SAML Response

Signature validation

Certificate configuration

Claims/attribute mapping

Timestamps

Audience / Issuer mismatch

🛠 Tools Used for Debugging

Senior engineers use:

✅ Browser DevTools

Network tab

Inspect POST to /auth/saml/callback

Copy SAMLResponse

✅ SAML Tracer (Browser Extension)

Very common tool for debugging SAML.

✅ Base64 Decoder

Because SAMLResponse is Base64 encoded.

✅ XML Formatter

To read decoded XML clearly.

🔁 Step-by-Step Debugging Process

When login fails:

Step 1️⃣ Capture the SAMLResponse

In browser network tab:

Look at:

POST /auth/saml/callback

Copy value of:

SAMLResponse=PHNhbWxwOlJlc3BvbnNl...
Step 2️⃣ Decode It

It’s Base64 encoded.

Decode → get XML.

Now you can see:

Issuer

Assertion

Signature

Attributes

Timestamps

🔐 Step 3️⃣ Check Signature Errors

Common error:

Invalid signature

Possible causes:

Wrong certificate configured

Certificate expired

IdP rotated cert

Using wrong environment (dev vs prod IdP)

⏰ Step 4️⃣ Check Timestamp Errors

Inside assertion:

<saml:Conditions
  NotBefore="2026-02-20T10:00:00Z"
  NotOnOrAfter="2026-02-20T10:05:00Z">

Common issues:

Server clock mismatch

Expired assertion

Clock skew not configured

Fix:

settings.allowed_clock_drift = 5 # seconds
🎯 Step 5️⃣ Check Audience Restriction

Inside XML:

<saml:Audience>https://yourapp.com</saml:Audience>

If your Rails issuer is:

https://app.company.com

Mismatch → validation fails.

🧩 Step 6️⃣ Check Issuer

If Rails expects:

https://adfs.company.com/adfs/services/trust

But XML has:

https://login.microsoftonline.com/xyz

It means:

Wrong IdP.

👥 Step 7️⃣ Debug Claim Mapping

Common issue:

User logs in but role missing.

Check:

<saml:Attribute Name="role">

Maybe IdP is sending:

http://schemas.microsoft.com/ws/2008/06/identity/claims/role

Instead of simple role.

So in Rails:

auth.extra.raw_info["http://schemas.microsoft.com/..."]

Mapping mismatch is very common.

🚨 Most Common Production Issues

Here are the top real-world SAML issues:

Problem	Root Cause
Invalid Signature	Wrong or rotated certificate
No user found	Email claim missing
Expired assertion	Clock mismatch
Audience mismatch	Wrong issuer configured
Infinite redirect loop	Session not being set
500 error in callback	Parsing failure
🧠 How to Debug in Rails

Enable debug logs:

OneLogin::RubySaml::Logging.logger = Rails.logger

Log request.env["omniauth.auth"]

Check:

auth = request.env["omniauth.auth"]
Rails.logger.info auth.inspect
